\subsubsection{Correlation Matrix}

Following is the correlation matrix for the continuous predictors in the data set. Note that while many of the predictors are correlated with one another, none exhibit a high degree of correlation with the response \textbf{Larea}.

It appears that \textbf{TrFFMC} and \textbf{ISI} are highly correlated (-0.7665), as well as \textbf{DC} and \textbf{DMC} (0.6825), \textbf{temp} and \textbf{TrFFMC} (-0.6047). Furthermore, \textbf{temp} and \textbf{DMC} have somewhat high linear correlation (0.4923),along with \textbf{temp} and \textbf{RH} (-0.4866), \textbf{temp} and \textbf{DC}(0.4886) and \textbf{TrFFMC} and \textbf{DMC} (-0.4847). Finally, \textbf{temp} and \textbf{ISI} appear to be somewhat linearly correlated (0.4417), along with \textbf{TrFFMC} and \textbf{DC} (0.4886).

